social_posts.post_text: Snowshoeing into the backcountry &  camping out in a yurt = 10/10 experience for the whole fam! Sweet little Flagstaff staycation this past weekend✨

Welcome to the world Madelynn Joy!!🥹 The last 36hours have been some of the most beautiful moments of my life: my sweet niece arrived at 2:45am yesterday and being there for her arrival was just the best💖 This little winter solstice baby has already brought so much joy & light to our lives✨ What a gift to be an Aunt!
Having some family in town for the week + a big snowstorm + 8days of Madelynn Joy = a very Merry Christmas!✨ Wishing everyone a joyful end to 2022!

Happy New Year!! Feeling a lot of hope & excitement heading into 2023 with the anticipation of Baby Smith arriving in April☺️❣️ 

Wishing everyone lots of love, joy & peace in the new year!

Headed to NY to celebrate the life & legacy of an amazing woman I was so lucky to call Grandma💛

Do you ever think of someone and your heart is immediately filled with warmth and your brain is flooded with joyful memories? Lorraine Schneider is unquestionably that type of person to me and to many others. Grandma was the queen of bringing people together and showing up for others in big and small ways. She was always active in her communities, steady in her faith, and had the absolute best sense of humor - always the first to laugh at jokes, especially if they were about her! Grandma would kick all our butts in tennis & solitaire into her 80s, and continued to play goalie during family soccer & hockey games even when she was wheelchair-bound. She had passion for travel, wine & martinis, gelato, going to museums & Broadway plays, and - most of all - for spending time with her family & friends. Her presence is going to be so missed, but her spirit, traditions, memories and unwavering love will undoubtedly live on for generations to come. To a life well-lived and to a human who embodied so much of what I hope to be✨

For me, happiness is so intertwined with physical and mental health. (Which I've learned is also super linked to gut health!) 

This past year consisted of some new challenges when it came to my health, and I've been so grateful to have the insights and support from Ixcela to help me optimize my physical and mental health. 

Through Ixcela's gut health test and regularly working with one of their amazing licensed performance dietitians, I’ve been better able to navigate supporting a healthy pregnancy and continue chasing my running goals (protein intake has been a big deal!).

And they've somehow made the process super easy and fun! Excited to continue working with them and totally encourage you to check them out no matter what your health or performance goals might be. 

If you want to see if Ixcela is a good fit for you - you can schedule a free 15-minute session with one of their Performance Registered Dietitians! Link in my bio.

📷: @theschultzee from NCAA XC Champs weekend back in Nov! (~18weeks🤰!)

From New York to Maine to Boston… such a happy 10days back East spending time with family & friends! Flying home and can’t help but smile that the next time I fly will likely be after baby girl’s arrival😊

Visited the new MLK ‘The Embrace’ statue in Boston Commons before leaving today and love the one quote that’s on it:
“Love is such a powerful force. 
It’s there for everyone to embrace - 
that kind of unconditional love for all of humankind.
That is the kind of love that impels people to go into the community and try to change conditions for others, 
to take risks for what they believe in.”

Running into week 30 and feelin good!*

Feels really good to be back in a rhythm at home! 6miles + drills & wickets w/ the crew on Monday; a fun 20x200m (@ :36-38) w/ some @hoka teammates yesterday; and on the @elliptigo_usa bike today!

*Or as good as I think I can at this point in pregnancy! Grateful to still be running and working out despite feeling a bit heavy, slow & tired!😅 Taking this final trimester day-by-day and listening to whatever my body feels is right (which definitely entails a lot more rest than usual💆‍♀️). #GrowBabyGrow #FlyHumanFly

What a weekend of track & field✨

Still buzzing from watching friends pour it out at USATF Indoor Champs! @nikkihiltz winning their first national title, @theschultzee running a personal best and finishing 5th in the 800m, @_ellyphant_ & @hannahsteelman_ going 4th & 7th in the 3k, and @naz_elite having a great showing!! Dreaming of being out there next year!

📷 (2 & 7): @007trackfan

Often in workouts I tell myself “one rep at a time” - in pregnancy I often find myself thinking “one day at a time.” The whole of something can feel incredibly daunting, but breaking it down into smaller increments somehow has the magic of making it seem more manageable (I’ll probably need to be reminded of that in labor😅). 

Approaching 33weeks and happy to still feel pretty good running in circles! It’s been a strange past few days (weeks) with some crazy snowstorms but just taking it day-by-day, listening to my body & adjusting as we go✨
Monday: 6miles + light drills & strides
Tuesday: 14x200m (@:36-37 w/ one at :33) and 1x400m (@:80) 
Wednesday & Thursday: shovel + rest🔁
Friday: 16x200m (@:36-39) - so happy syncing w/ @stephrothstein !
This weekend: 🤷‍♀️ tbd 

Wore my @hoka Guatemala shirt today because very excited for @luisgrijalva_ & Flag teammates/friends to race the Ten tomorrow night! Livestream & info at @soundrunning !
#FlyHumanFly 

🎥: @aldomarquez954 
🎵: Rihanna - do I have to explain why?!
Unanticipated trip back to Maine this past week - there’s nothing quite like family time✨💛

Happy 40th Anniversary to my beautiful parents❣️🍾

🥂 To two people whose love over the past 4 decades has had a profoundly positive impact on the lives of so many (know I speak for Brian, Kathy & Kevin too when I say it feels like we won the lottery when we were given you as parents)! Thank you for being such shining examples of love, loyalty, friendship & partnership❤️✨

Spring & April (& birth month!) are *finally* here!✨

Spent a good chunk of the day in Sedona w/ my little sister - passing out medals to all the awesome finishers at the @runflagstaff Sedona Stumble 5k & 10k, eating acai bowls, and exploring a new trail and seeing lots of signs of new life🌸 Couldn’t help but reflect on how last year I ran the Sedona Stumble 5k just a few weeks after a heartbreaking miscarriage and now, one year later, baby girl’s arrival will be within a few weeks🥹💖

Dogs have been majorly upping their nutrition game lately thanks to @nomnom ! Feels good to feed the furfam #freshfood with nothing but healthy ingredients. Get 50% off #NomNom with the link in my bio! #ad
Grateful for a sweet day-trip to our favorite area this past weekend✨ 38 weeks and can’t wait to become a family of *6*!

3 days ago our lives changed forever…
introducing Nova Katherine Smith✨
Born 4/19/23 and has already filled us with astronomical levels of love, joy & gratitude🥹💖

Happy due date little Nova! Dreamt of meeting you for a long time… 6 days into your life, it’s easy to say you are the best thing to ever happen to me💖
So grateful for the family & friends, near & far, who have showered us with so much love and well wishes!🙏
Last day of Big Sky Conference Championships and wishing we could be in Colorado to cheer on our favorite team! Let’s go @nautrackfieldxc !!🪓💛💙

Was already feeling inexplicably lucky when I woke up this morning, but then on our walk today we met this horned toad (a symbol of good luck)!!✨🥰

So much gratitude and love for Mike & Nova for giving me my most cherished title, for our own amazing moms, and all those that are examples of motherly love. 
Happy Mother’s Day💖 

📷: @jostevvens 🙏 for the wonderful walk & happy/toady pictures😄

And just like that… High School graduate🥹 So proud of Alyzabeth and the beautiful young woman she’s become. Exciting things ahead for her, but first: time to celebrate!! Huge congrats to the Class of ‘23 (especially for navigating through the extra adversities that the covid pandemic threw at your high school years)!🎓🖤

Time really flies… what a reminder to dream big but live in the present & love hard✨

What an incredible gift to have a good friend fly from across the country to help you while the hubs is outta town for work! Always cherish time with @samroecker but Nova (& the dogs) getting to be loved on by Aunt Sam was the best🥹🙏 Learn so many things from Sam that I want to emulate and/or pay forward✨

Gave birth 7 weeks ago, and today I got to do my first “real” run!! 4miles on the trails never felt so happy😊 

Started regularly using the AlterG at 4 weeks postpartum and added in walk/jogs right before 6 weeks. That - mixed with lots of walks, rehab exercises (thank you @jessica.w.dorrington for guiding me through pregnancy & postpartum!!), some biking & elliptigo, and all the Nova snuggles - has me excited to be taking baby steps towards running & racing again! Long way to go, and want to be cautious on this comeback, but feeling very optimistic and grateful to be at this point! And very much looking forward to more runs with friends!! 

Happy #globalrunningday ! #flyhumanfly

📸: @samroecker (AlterG)
📸: @shane_quinn92 (thanks for keeping me company on my first run back!)

Walks & wildflowers w/ family & friends lately have been✨ 

Started going for walks a few days after birth and it was my sole form of exercise for ~4weeks. 8weeks postpartum now and running up to 8miles on land! Continuing to mix in AlterG runs, biking, and walking - and very much enjoying it all! Very few photos from any of it but here are some happy walking ones💚
So grateful to be my father’s daughter, and so much joy watching Mike become a father - Nova and I sure are lucky! So much love for these two dads. Happy Father’s Day💙

Getting to run with friends plus do my first track workout (16x200m) this past week PLUS watching friends put in the final touches for USATF Champs next week = a magical feeling✨ 
#FlyHumanFly 

📸(1): @mr.nono500 
🎥(1): @emma_gee1777
What a week! Nova’s first flight (slept her way through a cross country redeye🙏) and meeting so much more of her family🥹 Feeling very fortunate for days like this💛

~90degrees + high humidity and they still happily join me for a track workout (even after staying up past midnight to watch USAs)🥹 

Strange to not be at USAs this year, but excitedly cheering from afar - and working towards fitness with family this month! 11weeks postpartum: 56miles run, a tempo workout, track session, and 14mile long run - almost every step of it with Brian, and the best help (s/o Mom & Kevin) with watching Nova! Happy with the progress and grateful for an amazing family😊

&dreaming of starting lines! 
#FlyHumanFly

Grateful for a fun 3nights of camping, biking & hiking around Acadia National Park with the fam✨ (And grateful that, at 12weeks old, Nova is pretty go-with-the-flow and did well sleeping in the back of a truck with me! Pretty special her first national park & camping trip are in Maine with her grandparents… showing her my roots young😊)!

Last day as a 31yr old - reflecting on a year that was hard in some major ways, but was also the year I became a mom so it’ll always be one of my absolute favorites & most rewarding✨💛 To the next lap around the sun (and more laps around the track😁)!

& happy happy birthday to the amazing running specialist / pelvic floor PT  @jessica.w.dorrington who has been such an incredible guide & friend throughout my pregnancy & postpartum journey🙏🫶

📷: @nicolerupephotography ✨

Lil training & racing update!

Last 7 days looked something like:
-73miles run
-First double threshold workout in awhile
-24x200m workout
-2x 16milers (avg sub-7 pace)

What those stats don’t show:
-The wild amount of time & energy that nursing & pumping take (breastfeeding is one of the most incredible bonding experiences ever, but comes w/ some challenges)
-Sleep is all over the place and tired feels like the norm 
-Doing more sessions at unideal times of day (ie midday when heat & humidity are peak) than I’d like to admit (sometimes an extra hour or two of sleep is irresistible)
-The amazing support of family making this all possible (& extra fun)
-The inexplicable love, joy & gratitude of getting to be Nova’s mom & a runner all at the same time!

14weeks postpartum and can’t believe how big (& smiley) Nova already is! Also can’t believe I get to jump in a race next weekend! So excited to line up for Maine’s iconic @tdbeach2beacon race again!! #flyhumanfly 

🎥: no photos or video from this past week but here’s a happy clip from a cooldown lap on my bday workout 7/18!

August is off to a pretty great start☀️

An 11mile workout followed by a beautiful walk around a Maine island & a little shopping + dinner in Freeport w/ my parents & Nova✨ (Nova’s first time facing outwards in the baby carrier and she was a big fan!😛)

SO much fun lining up for the 25th running of the @tdbeach2beacon 10k yesterday! An amazing event for so many reasons and particularly special to be a part of having been born & raised in Maine! This also felt like such a full-circle moment for me… last year when I raced here I didn’t know I was a few weeks pregnant (found out shortly after and haven’t really raced since). Fast forward to this year: 3.5 months postpartum, finished in 34:09 & 12th place - but felt like a winner. Long way to go in terms of getting back to where I want to be, but it’s a good start and I’m super excited for this new chapter in my running career! So much gratitude and joy for being Nova’s mom, being able to train & race again (I really missed being out there), and having so much incredible support from family & friends & @hoka ✨🙏💛 
#FlyHumanFly

Happy to be home & running around my favorite oval again! Even happier getting to share some warmup miles and feed off the good vibes of the @naz_elite crew this morning!✨

➡️ to see all the sweet @hoka shoes I used in today’s session. Loving the colorway and loving how they make me feel like I can fly again🦅 #FlyHumanFly

🎥/📷: @stephrothstein !

So fun getting to run the 46th annual Big Brothers Big Sisters Flagstaff Trail 1/2 Marathon this morning! Have wanted to do this race for years and it was as special as I imagined it to be. Incredible community event supporting an organization dear to my heart (@flagstaffbigs ); super well run by @natraneil @runflagstaff & awesome volunteers; and a beautiful, hilly, challenging course at 7000ft to get the legs & lungs burning! Already excited to do this one again!😁

*Regardless of where you live, highly encourage everyone to check out the @bbbsamerica organization - whether to sign a child up, volunteer to be a big, or looking for an impactful place to donate time or money - it can be life-changing in the best of ways✨

social_posts.post_text: Recently spent ~6weeks in Maine and feeling so grateful for lots of quality time with family & friends, especially while Nova is this little! Felt like she changed so much in those 6weeks - it’s true what they say: they grow so fast🥺 Special to slow down a bit and soak in the summer with loved ones✨

Big smiles after a 17mile double-threshold day (w/ 10miles of T) where Nova got to come to the second session thanks to Nikki & Emma volunteering to take care of her🥰🙏💜

Ended the day with helping put together some Pride5k packages with friends! If you haven’t signed up yet - get on it!🏃🌈✨

With Pre Classic being this weekend, I realized its been over two years since I’ve raced on the track (last one was Pre Classic 5k on 8/20/21 right after the Olympics) - kinda hard to believe. Have missed it so much. BUT happy to currently be stacking 80+ mile weeks with quality workouts (and a day of rest)! Feels good to be building fitness this Fall and very much looking forward to getting back on the track in 2024!✨

📷: @mr.nono500 from one of last week’s sessions!

Fun Friday at the track with friends who happily volunteer to hang with Nova when childcare falls through last minute🥲 Feeling lucky to have such amazing support in so many ways! And feeling excited to be stringing solid workouts, mileage, & consistent weeks/months of training together🧱 #Flyhumanfly
So happy & helpful having my parents in town the last 10days! Nothing quite like family time✨💛

Was channeling some of that NAU XC energy on their track this morning (those Wisco races🔥🪓👏)!! Nothing like some Vo2 mile reps followed by some faster shorter reps to bring my hands to my knees. Excited to be building fitness and very very excited for what the whole @nautrackfieldxc program is doing - it’s gonna be a fun Fall✨💙💛

🎥: @emma_gee1777 !

(G)olden days✨

A very fun friday getting to workout w/ @abdihamidnur @sarahall3 & @jeralynkiprotich ! Followed by going to the @runningupthemountainbook event - a historical account of @nautrackfieldxc that shares stories of what makes NAU & Flagstaff such a special place to be a runner💛💙

🎥: @emma_gee1777 after crushing her own workout!

Little throwback to last Saturday’s Soulstice trail run shenanigans! Was so fun being a part of the 24th edition of this amazing event put on by @natraneil ! A beautiful day of running & celebrating with Flag friends and watching the solar eclipse🌒✨ (& this year’s edition raised over $10k for @flagstaffbigs !!👏💛)

Also feels a bit crazy to think last year when I ran this I was ~13weeks pregnant with Nova and now she’s 6months old🥹 Time flies.

🎃season🧡

In between a 17mile double threshold day yesterday we took the kiddos to Viola’s Pumpkin Patch and I’m not sure who had more fun - the babies, the young boys or the moms! Lots of silliness & sweetness. Left feeling extra excited for holiday seasons as a mom🥰
The first of many years of Halloween ridiculousness together! Scary how fun it is to dress up your baby😅

Lucky to call this place & these people (& pups) *home*❤️

After 3 sweet months of not leaving Flagstaff once… November is full of travels. Gonna miss home, but so excited to race, go to NCAA XC nationals, & spend lots of time with family & friends in a variety of exciting places! First stop: NYC for 5k champs & marathon magic!

📷: a few favorite photos from some of our many family walks this fall✨

Running on joy and a heart filled with gratitude🙏

USATF Road 5k National Champs
2nd place, 15:26

Tough to capture what today meant to me in words. Last year during this weekend I was ~16weeks pregnant, cheering from the sidelines with competitive racing feeling far away. This year my 6month old daughter was by my side (& excitedly waiting to nurse after I finished; thank you USADA for letting her come to drug testing with me😅)! Being her mom and continuing to pursue my passion, while being so supported by family & friends (& @hoka !), is the absolute best✨ 

Perhaps the most special part of the day: hearing my dad cheering and getting to cool down with him around Central Park. Not many people are excited to run 2 days after their 8th round of chemo!

Thank you to @nyrr @abbottglobal & @usatf for putting on such a great event!
📸(1): @janemonti26.2

Welcome to NY (Nova’s version!)

Nova’s first visit to the big city was a memorable one (at least for her mom😋)! Our versions might be a little different but someday I’ll be telling her about our mother-daughter trip that included soaking in the city’s lights & sounds with my parents, spending time with family & friends, my return to racing, and witnessing the amazing energy of the NYC marathon! Here’s to hoping we can make it an annual trip🤞😁
#flyhumanfly

After a high-energy 3days in NYC last weekend, Nova and I were really happy to recharge in the beautiful state of Maine with the parents/grandparents this week!✨ Love showing Nova the area I was raised😊 

🚗➡️Boston bound for the BAA Half Marathon this weekend and to connect with more family & friends! #flyhumanfly

Went down to Boston this past weekend for a chilly & hilly Half marathon! Was with the lead pack for about half the race and then things went south and ran the last half solo👎 Finished in 1:12.36 - pretty stoked to be bummed with that right now. Know there’s lots of room for improvement and already very excited to try it again someday! But first I think I’ll go back to 1/13 of the distance (next race: THE Hawaii road mile!!)😁 #flyhumanfly 

Despite the rough race, the weekend was the happiest! Fun family time, got to watch my niece’s last soccer game of the season, and see my best friend / college roommate & her beautiful babies🥰 

Also felt really special that the B.A.A. Half is presented by the @thejimmyfund and @danafarber - where my dad is getting his cancer treatments. Cancer sucks. On so many levels. But my dad continues to model what living life to the fullest, showing up for others, and appreciating time, especially time with loved ones, looks like. While the race was the reason for the trip, I felt so grateful to check out the course with my dad a few days beforehand, have him out there biking to different points during the race, have his & my mom’s constant support with Nova, and share lots of simple & silly moments together throughout the trip. Definitely a race weekend I’ll cherish forever✨

Stumbled upon this sweet scene the other night and it made my heart so happy🥰

Grandpa was getting Nova extra ready to cheer on @nautrackfieldxc this weekend! So excited for these teams and so excited to be with our favorite guy after almost two weeks apart!!

✈️➡️Virginia for NCAA xc champs!!

Thanksgiving 2023 looked a little different than last year in some major ways… best of all is having Nova with us! Lots to be thankful for, especially this family of mine❤️ (& getting to spend it all together in Costa Rica✨)

Nova and I are happy to be back home in Flagstaff after ~3.5weeks away… but jeeze we enjoyed every single part of all our crazy travels! A major highlight of the trip was our time in Virginia with @nautrackfieldxc for the NCAA XC Championships! Two 2nd place team finishes in extremely exciting races to cap off absolutely incredible seasons for both the women’s & men’s teams!!👏 No words can capture how proud we are of Mike and the whole NAU program💛💙

Swipe to see a silly video of Nova keeping things light before the races (she laughed like that for a good 10mins) & last photo was from the very first xc meet of the season (Sep 2) - she did some good growing during the season!

Happyyyy to be back in Hawaiiiii!!! Especially with the babies🥹🥰

Stoke level is real high for the Kalakaua Merrie Mile tomorrow & some Island time after✨ Nova and I loved getting to meet baby Ivan, and I think Nova’s pretty into her new type of bib… (thanks @honolulumarathon for the cute surprise!).

Also feeling the feels because @nikkihiltz and I *finally* get to race together after being teammates for nearly 2years! Been dreamin of this start line!

Race goes off at 7:45am Hawaiian time - gonna be a fun one!🤙
#flyhumanfly

Hawaii, you hold a special place in our hearts!✨

Had a blast racing the Merrie Mile - huge thanks to @honolulumarathon for having me back out and putting on such an amazing event! Plus a few beautiful days in paradise w/ the fam… pretty incredible way to close out 2023 racing & traveling!🤙🙏

8months of Nova Katherine❣️

This girl has added so much joy to our lives. Grateful for her love and for all the people who love on her!🙏🫶

A few moments from this past week💖

A very merry week of work✔️

Last time I did a workout on an indoor track I was ~8months pregnant; now Nova is 8months old and holding the stopwatch🥺🥰 #timeflies #flyhumanfly 

Happy to be putting in some big training right now (and witnessing friends crush their’s!). Really excited for 2024 racing, but doing my best to continue to focus on enjoying this season of life and what each day holds. After 81miles/6days with some big workouts… time for a day off and to soak in some Christmas magic with the fam!

Wishing everyone a very happy holidays and lots of beautiful presence❣️

Christmas ‘23! Our first one as a family of three🥰 (Really six - dogs are family❣️) 
Heart is full🙏 Happy Holidays!

Ended 2023 in my favorite place with my favorite people❤️

Happy New Year!✨

Olympian🇺🇸
